-- Chicago’s Airport in Snowstorm Snarl
-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 2012-02-24T13:42:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-24/chicago-snowstorm-results-in-flight-cancellations-delays-at-two-airports.html
Due to a snowstorm moving through
the Chicago area, airlines at O’Hare and Midway International
Airports are reporting delays and cancellations, the Chicago
Department of Aviation said in an e-mailed statement.  At O’Hare, airlines are reporting delays averaging 45
minutes for all flights in and out of the airport. More than 150
flights have been cancelled due to weather, the department said.  At Midway, some flights are delayed up to 30 minutes, with
minor cancellations reported, the department said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  